    • simulateFishReproduction

      public static void simulateFishReproduction(ArrayList<SyntSpec.SSCarps> babyFish)
      splits males into wildtype and synthetic males. Then, gets a number of potential surviving offspring from each female. Potential offspring are aggregated and assigned a father, based on wildtype vs. synthetic fitness. Finally, actual offspring fish are created using makeBaby and added to babyFish
      Parameters:
      babyFish - empty array, will hold all baby fish

    • makeBaby

      public static SyntSpec.SSCarps makeBaby(int i, ArrayList<SyntSpec.SSCarps> potentialBabyFish, ArrayList<SyntSpec.SSCarps> mothers, ArrayList<SyntSpec.SSCarps> fathers)
      create a baby, using parent genotypes to call correct reproduction rules
      Parameters:
      i - the index of the mother, father, and baby lists to look at (to pull a specific combination of an already assigned mother/father/baby)
      potentialBabyFish - list of potential babyfish, of which we will use one
      mothers - list of potential mothers, of which we will use one
      fathers - list of potential fathers, of which we will use one
      Returns:
      a fish with the correct baby genotype, or null if no baby is produced from the mating

    • getReproduceType

      public static String getReproduceType(SyntSpec.SSGenomeCarps mom, SyntSpec.SSGenomeCarps dad)
      determine the reproduction type when both mom and dad are SSGenomeCarps
      Parameters:
      mom - SSGenomeCarps mom object
      dad - SSGenomeCarps dad object
      Returns:
      a string, to be parsed for reproduction. Options include "Trojan", "AlleleSailMC", "GeneDriveSexSkew", and "FLExtended"

    • reproduceMaternalCarryoverAS

      public static SyntSpec.SSGenomeCarps reproduceMaternalCarryoverAS(SyntSpec.SSGenomeCarps mom, SyntSpec.SSGenomeCarps dad, SyntSpec.SSGenomeCarps baby)
      create a baby when either the mother or the father carries an allele sail, and maternal carryover of editing is permitted. Learn more about the behavior in README.md
      Parameters:
      mom - an SSGenomeCarps mom object
      dad - an SSGenomeCarps dad object
      baby - a potential baby to be returned
      Returns:
      baby if offspring viable, null if the baby's generation is >= GENE_GENERATION_DEATH

    • reproduceGDMCSS

      create a baby when either parent has a gene drive element that causes sex skew. Maternal carryover of homing is permitted. Learn more about the behavior in README.md
      Parameters:
      mom - an SSGenomeCarps mom object
      dad - an SSGenomeCarps dad object
      baby - a potential baby to be returned

    • reproduceTrojan

      create a baby when either parent genotype contains "TROJANS", which causes all-male offspring. Learn more about the behavior in README.md, under the "YY Trojan"
      Parameters:
      mom - an SSGenomeCarps mom object
      dad - an SSGenomeCarps dad object

    • reproduceGeneral

      public static SyntSpec.SSGenomeCarps reproduceGeneral(SyntSpec.SSGenomeCarps mom, SyntSpec.SSGenomeCarps dad, SyntSpec.SSGenomeCarps baby)
      create a baby when neither parent has special behaviors. All alleles have equal probability of being inherited
      Parameters:
      mom - an SSGenomeCarps mom object
      dad - an SSGenomeCarps dad object
      baby - a potential baby to be returned
      Returns:

    • reproduceSSFL

      public static SyntSpec.SSFLCarps reproduceSSFL(SyntSpec.SSFLCarps mom, SyntSpec.SSFLCarps dad, SyntSpec.SSFLCarps baby)
      create a baby when either parent is SSFL, or has a genome of length six. If offspring carry a "p" and a "T", they are nonviable. If the offspring is female and carries an "L", they are also nonviable. Learn more about the behavior in README.md, under "Self-Stocking Incompatible Male System (SSIMS)"
      Parameters:
      mom - an SSGenomeCarps mom object
      dad - an SSGenomeCarps dad object
      baby - a potential baby to be returned
      Returns:
      baby if offspring viable, null if the baby's generation is >= GENE_GENERATION_DEATH or otherwise nonviable.

    • reproduceGD

      public static SyntSpec.GDCarps reproduceGD(SyntSpec.GDCarps mom, SyntSpec.GDCarps dad, SyntSpec.GDCarps baby)
      create a baby when either parent is a GDCarp (has a genome of length two). Individuals that are "GW" have a chance of converting the "W" into another allele. Offspring that are GG, GL, or LL will be nonviable. Learn more about the behavior in README.md, section "Synthetic Gene Drive (SGD)"
      Parameters:
      mom - an SSGenomeCarps mom object
      dad - an SSGenomeCarps dad object
      baby - a potential baby to be returned
      Returns:
      baby if offspring viable, null if the baby's generation is >= GENE_GENERATION_DEATH or otherwise nonviable.

    • reproduceAS

      public static SyntSpec.ASCarps reproduceAS(SyntSpec.ASCarps mom, SyntSpec.ASCarps dad, SyntSpec.ASCarps baby)
      create a baby when either of the parents is an ASCarp (has a genome of length 5). Offspring without an "F" allele are always male. Learn more about the behavior in README.md, section "Masculinizing Allele Sail"
      Parameters:
      mom - an SSGenomeCarps mom object
      dad - an SSGenomeCarps dad object
      baby - a potential baby to be returned
      Returns:
      baby if offspring viable, null if the baby's generation is >= GENE_GENERATION_DEATH or otherwise nonviable.
